org.mpxj

Class ProjectCalendar

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mpxj.ProjectCalendarDays
      • org.mpxj.ProjectCalendar
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProjectEntityWithMutableUniqueID, ProjectEntityWithUniqueID, TimeUnitDefaultsContainer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CombinedCalendar, TemporaryCalendar

    public class ProjectCalendar
extends ProjectCalendarDays
implements ProjectEntityWithMutableUniqueID, TimeUnitDefaultsContainer
    This class represents a Calendar Definition record. Both base calendars and calendars derived from base calendars are represented by instances of this class. The class is used to define the working and non-working days of the week. The default calendar defines Monday to Friday as working days.

      • getExpandedCalendarExceptionsWithWorkWeeks

        public List<ProjectCalendarException> getExpandedCalendarExceptionsWithWorkWeeks()
        Expand any exceptions in the calendar, and include any working weeks defined by this calendar as exceptions. This is typically used to communicate working time accurately when the consuming application does not have the concept of working weeks.
        Returns:
        List of calendar exceptions representing exceptions and working weeks

        public DayType getDayType(DayOfWeek day)
        Retrieve the day type. If this is a derived calendar and the day type is DEFAULT, recurse through the calendar hierarchy to find the effective day type. Note that if the calendar hierarchy has been incorrectly configured and that the base calendar defines the day as DEFAULT, this implementation will assume Saturday and Sunday are non-working days.
        Parameters:
        day - required day
        Returns:
        day type
